---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | PDF Toolkit"
  description="PDF Toolkit privacy policy. Your files never leave your device — all processing happens locally in your browser."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>No file you process ever leaves your device.</strong> PDF Toolkit runs entirely in your browser.
      When you merge, split, or rotate a PDF, the operation runs on your CPU using WebAssembly.
      Your files are never sent to any server — not even ours. You can verify this by opening your browser's
      DevTools → Network tab and confirming zero outbound requests during any operation.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      We do not collect any personal data. We may use privacy-respecting analytics
      (such as Plausible, which is cookie-free) to measure page visits in aggregate.
      We never track individual users, collect IP addresses, or store any information about the files you process.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We store a single <code>consent</code> key in <code>localStorage</code> to remember your cookie banner preference.
      This is not a tracking cookie and is never sent to any server.
    </p>
    <p>
      In the future, we may serve Google AdSense ads. If and when this happens, the cookie banner
      will be updated to reflect AdSense's cookie usage, and you will be asked to consent before any
      advertising cookies are set.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The app is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may log standard web server access logs
      (IP address, user agent, page visited) as part of their service. These logs are governed by
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions? Open an issue on our <a href="https://github.com/pdftoolkit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
